      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental hemolysis measurements must include at least three independent replicates per operating point with inter-replicate variability reported.",
      "rationale": "Five independent replicates performed per operating point using fresh porcine blood from separate donors. Inter-replicate coefficient of variation ranges from 8 % to 14 % across operating points; pooled uncertainty incorporated into validation metric. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Dimensionless similarity parameters (Reynolds number, flow coefficient) must match between validation experiments and COU operating points to within 10 %.",
      "rationale": "Reynolds number matching achieved at three of five operating points (deviation < 8 %). At the two highest-speed points, blood analogue viscosity mismatch results in Re deviation of 18–22 %. Flow coefficient matched within 5 % at all points. Achieved level 2 below required level 3; impact on NIH prediction assessed as bounded by sensitivity study."
    }
